docs.summary:
*
AccountDeletionProcess is the main entity of GdprAutomations that describes the automation flow of some delete account request

members.name: id
members.doc: AccountDeletionRequest ID

members.name: userGuid
members.doc: Represents the id of the user to be deleted

members.name: userConfirmation
members.doc: Represents the confirmation status provided by the user associated with the process

members.name: answersTicketId
members.doc: Represents the id of the corresponding wix answers ticket used to track and manage the request

members.name: createdDate
members.doc: Represents the time this AccountDeletionRequest was created

members.name: status
members.doc: Represents the status of the request in the automation flow

members.name: requestError
members.doc: Represents the error state of the request, that should be resolved

members.name: optOutDetails
members.doc: Represents an explicit admin request to block the request from being submitted for deletion

members.name: harvesterRequestId
members.doc: Represents the id of the corresponding deletion request created by the harvester once this request was submitted to the harvester

members.name: revision
members.doc: Represents the current state of an item. Each time the item is modified, its `revision` changes. for an update operation to succeed, you MUST pass the latest revision

members.name: updatedDate
members.doc: Represents the time this AccountDeletionRequest was last updated

docs.summary:
*
UserDetails is being used to provide support agents human readable visibility about the request via the wix answers ticket
This entity contains PII data which is only being used when opening the wix answers ticket upon an incoming request
This entity is not being saved in the db, nor being returned by the api

members.doc: Maximum number of items to return in the results.

members.name: cursor
members.doc:
Pointer to the next or previous page in the list of results.

Pass the relevant cursor token from the `pagingMetadata` object in the previous call's response.
Not relevant for the first request.

members.name: fieldName
members.doc: Name of the field to sort by.

members.name: order
members.doc: Sort order.

members.name: filter
sort
members.doc:
Sort object in the following format:
`[{"fieldName":"sortField1","order":"ASC"},{"fieldName":"sortField2","order":"DESC"}]`

members.name: fields
members.doc: Array of projected fields. A list of specific field names to return. If `fieldsets` are also specified, the union of `fieldsets` and `fields` is returned.

members.name: fieldsets
members.doc: Array of named, predefined sets of projected fields. A array of predefined named sets of fields to be returned. Specifying multiple `fieldsets` will return the union of fields from all sets. If `fields` are also specified, the union of `fieldsets` and `fields` is returned.

members.name: paging
members.doc: Paging options to limit and skip the number of items.

members.name: cursorPaging
members.doc: Cursor token pointing to a page of results. Not used in the first request. Following requests use the cursor token and not `filter` or `sort`.

docs.summary:
Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN - Required default
  • UN_CONFIRMED - Un-Confirmed
  • CONFIRMED - Confirmed

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN - Required default
  • FREE - Represents a free users account
  • PREMIUM - Represents a premium users account - currently not supported by automations service
  • NO_WEBSITE - Represents a no website users account - currently not supported by automations service

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN - Required default
  • REQUEST_OF_INFORMATION - Request of information by legal authorities
  • OTHER

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN - Required default
  • FAILED_TO_CREATE_TICKET
  • FAILED_TO_NOTIFY_USER_REQUEST_CREATED - Represents a failure to notify the user that his deletion request has been created
  • FAILED_TO_BLOCK_ACCOUNT - Represents a failure to block the users account
  • FAILED_TO_NOTIFY_USER_ACCOUNT_BLOCKED - Represents a failure to notify the user that his account has been blocked
  • FAILED_TO_ADD_NOTE_TO_ACCOUNT - Represents a failure to add a note to users account in the user manager
  • FAILED_TO_UNBLOCK_ACCOUNT - Represents a failure to unblock the users account
  • FAILED_TO_NOTIFY_USER_ACCOUNT_UNBLOCKED - Represents a failure to notify the user that his account has been unblocked
  • FAILED_TO_INTERNALLY_NOTIFY_EMERGENCY_OPT_OUT - Represents a failure to internally notify the support agents via wix answers that the account has been successfully opted out
  • FAILED_TO_PERMANENT_DELETE_USER - Represents a failure to submit the user for permanent deletion

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN - Required default
  • CREATED - Represents a deletion request submitted to out service
  • OPTED_OUT - Represents a deletion request which was opted out by the legal team
  • CANCELED - Represents a deletion request which was canceled on behalf of the user
  • ELIGIBLE_FOR_GDPR_DELETION - Represents a deletion request which successfully completed all required steps before deletion
  • INITIATED_GDPR_DELETION - Represents a deletion request which was sent to the gdpr harvester for deletion
  • COMPLETED_GDPR_DELETION - Represents a deletion request which was deleted successfully by the gdpr harvester
  • FAILED - Represents a deletion request which failed to completed all required steps before deletion

`NullValue` is a singleton enumeration to represent the null value for the `Value` type union. The JSON representation for `NullValue` is JSON `null`. Possible values are:
  • NULL_VALUE - Null value.
